 "awd_abstract_narration": "This research focuses on the development of high  precision tracking devices.  These will be part of large  scale particle physics detectors operating at the highest  machine energies available.  These devices, which use  silicon as the detecting element, will help physicists  reconstruct the details of how particles decay.  This, in  turn, will lead to an increased understanding of the physics  processes involved.  The ultimate goal of these experiments  is to discover the Higgs particle - the `missing link` of  the Standard Model of particle physics.  The technology  needed to make these devices work is at the cutting edge.  Its successful development will lead to applications in many  other fields of science and industry.  The PI will directly  involve undergraduates in this research, preparing them for  careers in many high-tech industries.  This award will also  help fund her outreach program directed at women in high  schools.",
